Subject: Derived Boundary Delineation Worker Latch Source

Description: Preserved derived source for the property-line, non-placeholder, and ASCII latches observed during boundary_delineation_010 LM Studio worker benchmarking.

& [DerivedBoundaryDelineationWorkerLatchSource] is preserved derived source
  + [source_type] is derived_from_benchmark_observation
  + [observed_subject] is corpus_boundary_delineation_010
  + [initial_failure] is worker used SOP-looking property fields but replaced the literal is operator with separates, includes, or reminds
  + [first_retry_failure] is worker copied ellipsis placeholders instead of filling field content
  + [second_retry_failure] is worker filled fields but produced non-ASCII punctuation that arrived as mojibake in captured SOP
  + [accepted_retry] is retry 003 passed exact property operator, non-placeholder content, ASCII output, required terms, forbidden terms, and outside preservation
  + [derived_latches] is property_line_latch, non_placeholder_latch, ascii_stability_check
  + [reason_for_change] is validator and prompt layers must catch form, content, and encoding faults before worker output can become readiness evidence
  + [outside] is hidden model state, broad LM Studio competence, project-root authority, and worker mutation authority

  = must: preserve each failed attempt as benchmark data
  = must: treat retry success as one family signal only
  = must: keep Codex as validator and integration authority
  - never: treat syntax success with hollow content as worker comprehension
